# Frontend Engineering (Next.js)

Apps: `apps/marketing/` (SSR/SSG), `apps/dashboard/` (CSR + Server Components), `apps/widget/` (embed).

## Layer Rules

- **Presentation only** — no business logic in components.
- Call backend via `packages/api-client` or typed fetch wrappers.
- Validate forms client-side for UX; **server validates authoritatively**.
- Use shared UI from `packages/ui` when available.

## Conventions

- Functional components with TypeScript.
- Colocate component-specific hooks; extract reusable hooks to `hooks/`.
- Use Tailwind for styling; follow existing design tokens.
- Handle loading, error, and empty states explicitly.
- Auth state via secure cookies/tokens — never store secrets in localStorage.

## Marketing vs Dashboard

| App | Rendering | Purpose |
|-----|-----------|---------|
| `apps/marketing` | SSR/SSG | SEO, landing, public pages |
| `apps/dashboard` | CSR-heavy | Authenticated app shell |
| `apps/widget` | Minimal bundle | Embeddable chat widget |

## Do Not

- Duplicate API business rules in the frontend.
- Call MongoDB, Redis, or OpenAI from frontend code.
- Skip accessibility (semantic HTML, labels, keyboard nav).
